European countries with difference in employment gap rates

Top five countries with highest gender employment gap rate in Europe are: Turkey, North Macedonia, Greece, Italy, Romania.

Top five countries with lowest gender employment gap rate in Europe are: Lithuania, Finland, Latvia, Sweden, Norway.

Top five countries with employment gap decreased the most in percentage points in Europe are: Lithuania, Latvia, Estonia, Cyprus, Finland.
